            <h2><strong>Percent of Ideal Body Weight (PIBW)</strong></h2>
            <p>
                Percent of Ideal Body Weight (PIBW) is a measure that compares an individual's current weight to their ideal body weight, which is the weight range that is considered healthy for them based on their height, age, and gender. 
                It is often used in clinical settings to monitor the nutritional status of patients, particularly those who are underweight or have experienced significant weight loss.
                Remember that it is always best to consult with a healthcare professional for an accurate assessment of your health.
            </p>
            <p>
                <h3>How is PIBW calculated?</h3><br>
                The formula for calculating PIBW is: <br>
                <strong>PIBW = (Current weight / Ideal body weight) x 100% </strong><br>
                *How is ideal body weight calculated? <br>
                <b>Men:</b> height(m) * height(m) * 22 <br>
                <b>Women:</b> height(m) * height(m) * 21 <br>
                For example, if a woman's height is 172cm (=1.72m), her ideal body weight is 1.72 * 1.72 * 21.
            </p>
            <p>
                <h3>What can PIBW tell you about your health?</h3>
                <br>
                Percent of Ideal Body Weight (PIBW) is used to gain insights regarding your nutritional status. 
                For example, if an individual's ideal body weight is 120 pounds and their current weight is 100 pounds, their PIBW would be calculated as:
                PIBW = (100 / 120) x 100% = 83.3% 
                In this case, the individual's PIBW is 83.3%, indicating that they are below their ideal body weight and may require additional nutritional support. <br>
