            <p>
                <h3>What is a limitation of WHR?</h3><br>
                Although waist circumference (WC) and waist-to-hip ratio (WHR) are commonly used methods for measuring abdominal obesity, it is important to note that they do not provide an accurate measurement of visceral fat. 
                Imaging techniques such as abdominal CT scanning are more effective in assessing visceral fat.
            </p>
